theorem
Th14: (n > ( 0 ) implies (ex X st ((X is non degenerate & X is  simplified) & ( 4 * n ) in X)))
proof
set b = ( 1 * ( ( 2 * 1 ) * ( 2 * n ) ) );
set c = ( 1 * ( ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) + ( 1 ^2 ) ) );
assume A1: n > ( 0 );
then n >= ( ( 0 ) + 1 ) by NAT_1:13;
then A2: ( n + n ) > ( ( 0 ) + 1 ) by XREAL_1:8;
then ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) > ( 1 ^2 ) by SQUARE_1:16;
then ( ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) - ( 1 ^2 ) ) > ( 0 ) by XREAL_1:50;
then reconsider a = ( 1 * ( ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) - ( 1 ^2 ) ) ) as (Element of ( NAT )) by INT_1:3;
reconsider X = { a,b,c } as Pythagorean_triple by A2,CKB29:def 1;
take X;
(a <> ( 0 ) & b <> ( 0 )) by A1;
hence (not ( 0 ) in X) by ENUMSET1:def 1;
( a - c ) = ( - 2 );
then ( a gcd c ) = ( ( 1 * ( ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) + ( 1 ^2 ) ) ) gcd ( - 2 ) ) by PREPOWER:97
.= ( ( abs ( 1 * ( ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) + ( 1 ^2 ) ) ) ) gcd ( abs ( - 2 ) ) ) by INT_2:34
.= ( ( abs ( 1 * ( ( ( 2 * n ) ^2 ) + ( 1 ^2 ) ) ) ) gcd ( abs 2 ) ) by COMPLEX1:52
.= ( ( ( 2 * ( 2 * ( n ^2 ) ) ) + 1 ) gcd 2 ) by INT_2:34
.= ( 1 gcd 2 ) by EULER_1:16
.= 1 by WSIERP_1:8;
then A3: a,c are_relative_prime  by INT_2:def 3;
(a in X & c in X) by ENUMSET1:def 1;
hence X is  simplified by A3,CKB33:def 1;
thus thesis by ENUMSET1:def 1;
end;
